 While the benefits of garlic tea are questionable, the ingredients used to make garlic tea have been shown to positively affect health. Garlic is high in potent compounds that possess anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. These include garlic, ginger, lemon, and honey. Honey is a beloved sweetener that people also commonly used as a natural remedy for coughs and congestion. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Chop garlic and let it stand for 10 minutes. Step 2 Bring water to a boil, then add chopped garlic, reduce the heat and simmer the mixture for 5â€“10 minutes. You can leave the chopped garlic in the tea or strain it out. Step 3 Mix in lemon juice and add honey to taste. You could also add some freshly grated or powdered ginger, depending on your taste preferences.